WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:08.970 --> 00:00:10.920
- Gold mining in South Africa,

00:00:10.920 --> 00:00:13.620
it is an industry that is centuries old.

00:00:15.150 --> 00:00:17.520
People are risking everything

00:00:17.520 --> 00:00:19.470
to support themselves and their families.

00:00:21.150 --> 00:00:24.817
- Desperate pleas from two
kilometers underground,

00:00:24.817 --> 00:00:26.542
hundreds of people are trapped

00:00:26.542 --> 00:00:28.691
in this mine in South Africa.

00:00:37.290 --> 00:00:39.930
- People are dying here.
Please help, please, please.

00:00:45.570 --> 00:00:50.070
- How many days must you
live in a situation like this?

00:00:57.390 --> 00:00:59.898
- This footage is showing
piles of dead

00:00:59.898 --> 00:01:01.489
and starving people.

00:01:11.460 --> 00:01:13.585
- We must call this
what it is.

00:01:13.585 --> 00:01:16.500
This is a Stilfontein massacre.

00:01:16.500 --> 00:01:17.550
- Illegal mining

00:01:17.550 --> 00:01:21.900
and gold theft have cost
the country 41 billion rand.

00:01:21.900 --> 00:01:25.470
Illegal mining is not a mining activity,

00:01:25.470 --> 00:01:27.660
but a criminal activity.

00:01:27.660 --> 00:01:29.388
It is a war on the economy.

00:01:36.073 --> 00:01:38.280
- We're not sending help to criminals.

00:01:38.280 --> 00:01:40.397
We're going to smoke them out.

00:02:51.450 --> 00:02:54.780
- Mining is a big deal in
South Africa, even though

00:02:54.780 --> 00:02:57.503
as an industry it's in decline.

00:02:58.528 --> 00:03:02.380
- As of 2024, there are

00:03:02.380 --> 00:03:06.280
around 6,200 abandoned or derelict mines.

00:03:06.280 --> 00:03:07.780
They're no longer profitable.

00:03:07.780 --> 00:03:10.030
The mining companies up and leave.

00:03:10.030 --> 00:03:11.890
The illegal miners then enter

00:03:11.890 --> 00:03:13.965
to take whatever minimal deposits

00:03:13.965 --> 00:03:15.670
may be left in that space

00:03:15.670 --> 00:03:19.003
to support themselves and their families.

00:04:17.680 --> 00:04:18.580
- At some point

00:04:18.580 --> 00:04:21.938
people started calling
illegal miners zama zamas.

00:04:21.938 --> 00:04:23.979
A direct translation would be

00:04:23.979 --> 00:04:25.840
to try and try again.

00:04:25.840 --> 00:04:27.730
You don't have a job.
You don't have a means

00:04:27.730 --> 00:04:28.960
to feed your family,

00:04:28.960 --> 00:04:31.120
and so you're trying whatever you can

00:04:31.120 --> 00:04:33.010
to make things work, to make ends meet.

00:05:41.475 --> 00:05:43.960
The South African government
currently estimates

00:05:43.960 --> 00:05:45.670
that they're losing potentially

00:05:45.670 --> 00:05:48.400
around 60 billion rand in revenue

00:05:48.400 --> 00:05:51.790
because of illegal mining that
happens across the country.

00:05:54.520 --> 00:05:59.000
Operation Vala Umgodi
is a multidisciplinary

00:05:59.000 --> 00:06:00.200
law enforcement operation.

00:06:01.370 --> 00:06:06.260
It is a project to crack
down on illegal mining.

00:06:07.370 --> 00:06:09.944
In August, 2024, Vala Umgodi

00:06:09.944 --> 00:06:11.902
officially came to Stilfontein.

00:06:13.848 --> 00:06:16.820
- The Vala Umgodi task team
are blocking routes used

00:06:16.820 --> 00:06:18.086
to deliver food in their

00:06:18.086 --> 00:06:20.990
operation against illegal mining.

00:06:20.990 --> 00:06:23.180
- The number of miners remaining

00:06:23.180 --> 00:06:25.597
underground is still unknown.

00:06:43.160 --> 00:06:45.980
- We have identified certain shafts used

00:06:45.980 --> 00:06:48.560
by these illegal miners
to take food underground.

00:06:48.560 --> 00:06:50.180
They're not getting a chance now

00:06:50.180 --> 00:06:52.763
to use those particular shafts.

00:07:21.328 --> 00:07:23.002
- Vala Umgodi had been happening

00:07:23.002 --> 00:07:24.800
for about a year at that point

00:07:24.800 --> 00:07:28.010
around the country where
they had used similar tactics

00:07:28.010 --> 00:07:31.490
of choking supply and people
had simply resurfaced.

00:07:31.490 --> 00:07:34.760
But what was different
about Stilfontein is the

00:07:34.760 --> 00:07:36.920
architecture of that shaft.

00:07:36.920 --> 00:07:41.909
It is literally a two
kilometer drop into the earth.

00:07:41.909 --> 00:07:44.857
If people above ground are
not able to pull you up,

00:07:44.857 --> 00:07:47.557
there is no way for you to get out.

00:08:42.860 --> 00:08:45.890
- If you move from one shaft to another,

00:08:45.890 --> 00:08:47.810
there's no infrastructure
to move between the two.

00:08:47.810 --> 00:08:51.050
So you're basically
wriggling through a tunnel,

00:08:51.050 --> 00:08:53.450
but the tunnel is flooded.

00:08:54.410 --> 00:08:58.920
There are boulders and things
sticking out from all angles.

00:08:58.920 --> 00:09:00.690
Bear in mind that you are hungry,

00:09:00.690 --> 00:09:04.800
so your physical strength
is obviously non-existent

00:09:04.800 --> 00:09:05.933
at that point.

00:09:05.933 --> 00:09:08.982
It was physically demanding

00:09:08.982 --> 00:09:10.620
For some it took days.

00:09:10.620 --> 00:09:12.670
Only a very small group of them

00:09:12.670 --> 00:09:13.803
were actually able to make

00:09:13.803 --> 00:09:15.675
that journey successfully.

00:12:17.830 --> 00:12:21.400
- Illegal mining is not a mining activity,

00:12:21.400 --> 00:12:25.990
but a criminal activity and
it is a war on the economy.

00:12:25.990 --> 00:12:29.320
- Illegal mining is such a divisive issue.

00:12:29.320 --> 00:12:33.580
The mining companies are
losing money from the shafts

00:12:33.580 --> 00:12:34.930
which are still operational.

00:12:34.930 --> 00:12:36.310
So from a government perspective,

00:12:36.310 --> 00:12:38.320
you're losing a lot of revenue, right?

00:12:38.320 --> 00:12:40.540
- Those people who are committing acts

00:12:40.540 --> 00:12:42.580
of criminality will want

00:12:42.580 --> 00:12:46.150
to hide away from law
enforcement agencies.

00:12:46.150 --> 00:12:49.450
- The majority of illegal
miners are foreign nationals

00:12:49.450 --> 00:12:51.250
who are undocumented.

00:12:51.250 --> 00:12:54.460
- Members of the defence force
arrested more than 80 illegal

00:12:54.460 --> 00:12:55.630
mining suspects.

00:12:55.630 --> 00:12:58.270
This area has long been
experiencing violent crimes

00:12:58.270 --> 00:13:01.420
suspected to be linked
to zama zama turf wars.

00:13:01.420 --> 00:13:02.800
- You do get the organised syndicates

00:13:02.800 --> 00:13:04.330
that have spotted an opportunity.

00:13:04.330 --> 00:13:07.968
They are gangs that are
terrorizing communities.

00:13:07.968 --> 00:13:09.909
- Theses zama zamas were

00:13:09.909 --> 00:13:13.390
disrupting life of citizens there.

00:13:13.390 --> 00:13:15.640
- Everybody is worried about their safety.

00:13:15.640 --> 00:13:18.465
We've had previous police officers killed.

00:13:18.465 --> 00:13:22.930
- We want stability, we
want order, we want peace.

00:13:29.410 --> 00:13:34.410
- Initially, the reports
were that people were

00:13:34.720 --> 00:13:37.870
staging some kind of a sit-in underground,

00:13:37.870 --> 00:13:40.240
that these were just
entitled people that didn't

00:13:40.240 --> 00:13:41.073
want to be arrested,

00:13:41.073 --> 00:13:42.881
and so there
was no sympathy at all.

00:13:44.920 --> 00:13:49.030
- We cut off the food,
water and necessity supply.

00:13:49.030 --> 00:13:52.180
We are quite confident that
with this particular strategy,

00:13:52.180 --> 00:13:53.920
they will be forced to come up.

00:13:55.360 --> 00:13:56.380
- Why should they be helped?

00:13:56.380 --> 00:14:00.580
Why should state resources be
committed to assisting people

00:14:00.580 --> 00:14:03.580
that were robbing the country of revenue?

00:14:04.690 --> 00:14:06.370
- You want us to send help to criminals.

00:14:06.370 --> 00:14:10.120
Honestly, we're not
sending help to criminals.

00:14:10.120 --> 00:14:12.490
We're going to smoke them
out. They will come out.

00:14:13.630 --> 00:14:16.990
- But actually the police
are refusing to help people

00:14:16.990 --> 00:14:19.210
that are trapped underground,

00:14:19.210 --> 00:14:21.190
not just refusing to resurface.

00:15:02.480 --> 00:15:05.930
- What you do see now is
community members stepping in

00:15:05.930 --> 00:15:07.790
and demanding to go

00:15:07.790 --> 00:15:11.125
and rescue these illegal
miners themselves.

00:15:12.080 --> 00:15:15.170
- You can't just come and
stand on top of the shaft

00:15:15.170 --> 00:15:16.970
while people that are alive.

00:15:18.140 --> 00:15:21.800
Even if you are dead,
you must be taken out.

00:15:22.820 --> 00:15:26.240
- A group of 50 men from the
community signed indemnity

00:15:26.240 --> 00:15:29.540
forms and started pulling
up illegal miners underground

00:15:29.540 --> 00:15:32.732
while others are watching from a distance.

00:16:40.305 --> 00:16:42.400
- We are here at Shaft 11.

00:16:42.400 --> 00:16:44.270
the operation has been halted.

00:16:44.270 --> 00:16:46.640
- The minister of police
say that the current efforts

00:16:46.640 --> 00:16:50.473
that are being used by
the locals are not safe.

00:17:21.380 --> 00:17:24.080
- As Christmas and Hanukkah
approach, activists

00:17:24.080 --> 00:17:26.480
and families say they cannot
celebrate while the miners

00:17:26.480 --> 00:17:28.490
remain in darkness and starving.

00:17:28.490 --> 00:17:31.580
- The state has told the
High Court in Pretoria

00:17:31.580 --> 00:17:34.340
that the Stilfontein
miners are not trapped,

00:17:34.340 --> 00:17:35.960
but evading arrest.

00:17:54.060 --> 00:17:56.010
- What government told us, they said,

00:17:56.010 --> 00:17:57.330
these are criminals underground.

00:17:57.330 --> 00:17:58.950
We will not give them assistance.

00:17:58.950 --> 00:18:00.420
- Those who don't want
to get out, it's simply

00:18:00.420 --> 00:18:02.850
because they're avoiding arrest.

00:18:02.850 --> 00:18:04.374
- We are allowing for
a situation where

00:18:04.374 --> 00:18:05.850
a significant number

00:18:05.850 --> 00:18:08.683
of lives are are going to be lost.

00:19:24.480 --> 00:19:26.520
- We must call this what it is now.

00:19:27.390 --> 00:19:29.430
This is a Stilfontein massacre.

00:19:39.625 --> 00:19:42.000
- I think government
came to the realisation

00:19:42.000 --> 00:19:43.980
that there was this tragedy unfolding

00:19:43.980 --> 00:19:45.530
because it is the police

00:19:45.530 --> 00:19:46.922
stopping people from providing them

00:19:46.922 --> 00:19:48.870
with supplies and from bringing them up,

00:19:48.870 --> 00:19:51.210
and so I think that also
motivated the courts

00:19:51.210 --> 00:19:53.580
to then compel government

00:19:53.580 --> 00:19:55.800
to allow the formal rescue operation.

00:20:00.383 --> 00:20:02.220
- The North Gauteng
High Court ordered

00:20:02.220 --> 00:20:04.830
that mine rescue services begin operations

00:20:04.830 --> 00:20:06.270
to rescue illegal miners.

00:20:09.990 --> 00:20:12.270
Is underway for 10 days.

00:20:12.270 --> 00:20:16.080
Then after 10 days, we'll
stop to assess.

00:20:16.080 --> 00:20:17.760
- It's quite an advanced
machine that we're using.

00:20:17.760 --> 00:20:19.500
The cage has got a camera at the bottom.

00:20:19.500 --> 00:20:21.030
It's got a camera inside the cage

00:20:21.030 --> 00:20:23.010
and also in the top we can
see whether there's any

00:20:23.010 --> 00:20:24.960
obstructions or whether
it's safe to raise or lower

00:20:24.960 --> 00:20:26.210
the conveyance.

00:21:01.900 --> 00:21:03.242
- National Police spokesperson

00:21:03.242 --> 00:21:04.450
Athlenda Mathe says

00:21:04.450 --> 00:21:06.550
officers will not be going underground

00:21:06.550 --> 00:21:08.066
to rescue illegal miners

00:21:08.066 --> 00:21:09.532
at a mine in Stilfontein.

00:21:09.532 --> 00:21:11.410
Mathe says the zama zamas

00:21:11.410 --> 00:21:14.770
could be heavily armed, posing
a serious risk to officers.

00:21:14.770 --> 00:21:16.210
- As a responsible government,

00:21:16.210 --> 00:21:18.310
we are not going to be allowing our men

00:21:18.310 --> 00:21:21.687
and women in blue as well as
our soldiers to go down there.

00:21:24.160 --> 00:21:27.820
- The police themselves
refused to go down underground

00:21:27.820 --> 00:21:29.170
because there was anxieties

00:21:29.170 --> 00:21:31.510
and fears around what they
would find, if they would be

00:21:31.510 --> 00:21:34.150
walking into a war zone,

00:21:34.150 --> 00:21:36.160
and so they needed volunteers essentially

00:21:36.160 --> 00:21:37.570
from the community.

00:21:37.570 --> 00:21:41.350
Mandla was one of those
guys that was a part of

00:21:41.350 --> 00:21:43.145
that operation.

00:21:43.145 --> 00:21:44.320
- Mandla Charles is saying that

00:21:44.320 --> 00:21:46.303
he's willing to go down

00:21:46.303 --> 00:21:48.760
and assist in terms of
ensuring that those that are

00:21:48.760 --> 00:21:51.340
underground are able to be pulled onto

00:21:51.340 --> 00:21:52.190
the service.

00:24:07.100 --> 00:24:11.180
- The most chilling aspect of
it was seeing the amount of

00:24:11.180 --> 00:24:13.250
forensic pathology vehicles,

00:24:13.250 --> 00:24:16.550
vehicles that were there
to collect dead bodies,

00:24:16.550 --> 00:24:20.300
and to see how many of
them were going in and out.

00:24:20.300 --> 00:24:24.170
It was just such a
strong, sickening stench

00:24:24.170 --> 00:24:26.900
and that points to just
how badly decomposed

00:24:26.900 --> 00:24:28.400
those bodies were.

00:26:03.965 --> 00:26:06.290
- From the community perspective,

00:26:06.290 --> 00:26:08.030
I think it was mostly a sense of defeat

00:26:08.030 --> 00:26:10.550
because they'd been screaming
at the top of their lungs

00:26:10.550 --> 00:26:14.300
for months that this
tragedy was unfolding.

00:26:15.535 --> 00:26:19.310
I think there's a sense that it's kind

00:26:19.310 --> 00:26:23.420
of been forgotten and that
government has gotten away

00:26:23.420 --> 00:26:24.622
scot-free.

00:26:26.363 --> 00:26:28.610
People lost breadwinners.

00:26:28.610 --> 00:26:30.917
The ecosystem has shut down.

00:26:30.917 --> 00:26:32.025
The residents there

00:26:32.025 --> 00:26:34.760
described Stilfontein as a ghost town.

00:26:34.760 --> 00:26:38.427
The economy was basically
shut down in a day.

00:28:03.315 --> 00:28:05.280
- Gold mining in South Africa,

00:28:05.280 --> 00:28:08.280
it is an industry that is centuries-old.

00:28:08.280 --> 00:28:11.190
Families are involved in
mining throughout generations.

00:28:11.190 --> 00:28:13.023
Given that it's a sunset industry,

00:28:13.023 --> 00:28:14.414
there aren't as many jobs

00:28:14.414 --> 00:28:15.630
as they were before.

00:28:15.630 --> 00:28:17.430
When you speak to people, they'll tell you

00:28:17.430 --> 00:28:19.110
that they are being attacked

00:28:19.110 --> 00:28:20.610
for doing the best that they can do.

00:28:20.610 --> 00:28:23.160
The alternative to what
they're doing would be crime.

00:28:24.570 --> 00:28:26.880
Illegal miners, zama zamas like Mandla

00:28:26.880 --> 00:28:31.050
and others, they've not been
able to feed their families

00:28:31.050 --> 00:28:32.158
for months.

00:28:32.158 --> 00:28:33.216
And they're so defiant.

00:28:33.216 --> 00:28:35.610
You'll hear them telling you
that the minute the police

00:28:35.610 --> 00:28:38.340
leave that shaft, they
will be back underground.

00:28:38.340 --> 00:28:40.260
They're not going to think twice about it.

00:28:40.260 --> 00:28:43.830
And the story really
highlights the legacy issue

00:28:43.830 --> 00:28:46.580
around gold mining in particular.

00:33:23.480 --> 00:33:25.250
- I think from a community
aspect, they're looking

00:33:25.250 --> 00:33:26.725
for some sense of acknowledgement

00:33:26.725 --> 00:33:27.808
from the government.

00:33:29.180 --> 00:33:31.040
Some form of compensation for the loss

00:33:31.040 --> 00:33:32.180
of life that occurred there.

00:33:34.580 --> 00:33:37.010
- We are here as

00:33:37.010 --> 00:33:38.010
victims.

00:33:38.900 --> 00:33:41.480
Those people died underground

00:33:41.480 --> 00:33:46.070
and nothing happens as of
today nobody's in jail.

00:33:46.070 --> 00:33:49.340
- But it's also I think, a very real anger

00:33:49.340 --> 00:33:52.190
that this is their way of living.

00:33:52.190 --> 00:33:54.470
And government refuses
to acknowledge that.

00:34:05.930 --> 00:34:08.480
- There have been longstanding
calls from groups

00:34:08.480 --> 00:34:11.120
to say formalize artisanal mining.

00:34:11.120 --> 00:34:14.020
It's something that happens
elsewhere in the world.

00:34:14.020 --> 00:34:17.128
When you speak to some of
theses zama zamas,

00:34:17.128 --> 00:34:18.573
not all of them are

00:34:18.573 --> 00:34:21.380
for the formalization

00:34:21.380 --> 00:34:25.340
because they feel that they may not get

00:34:25.340 --> 00:34:28.130
the rewards or profit that
they're getting at the moment.

00:34:28.130 --> 00:34:30.050
Most of them are just
saying, "Just leave us alone."

00:34:30.050 --> 00:34:32.840
You failed in your
mandates to provide jobs

00:34:32.840 --> 00:34:35.523
or environments that create
jobs for us to be able to work

00:34:35.523 --> 00:34:37.822
and provide for our families.
So just leave us be.

00:34:58.935 --> 00:35:00.603
- Stop killing our people!

00:35:01.695 --> 00:35:04.695
Stop killing the people of Stilfontein!

00:35:05.840 --> 00:35:07.415
We have trusted you with

00:35:07.415 --> 00:35:11.285
our votes, but you have sold us out

00:35:11.285 --> 00:35:13.709
and there is only one solution.

00:35:13.709 --> 00:35:14.785
- Revolution!

00:35:14.785 --> 00:35:17.135
- One solution!
- Revolution!

00:35:17.135 --> 00:35:18.893
- One solution!
- Revolution!

00:35:53.100 --> 00:35:57.125
- We commit the body to the ground.

00:35:58.535 --> 00:35:59.565
- Earth to earth.

00:36:00.975 --> 00:36:04.725
Ashes to ashes, dust to dust.

